Step-by-Step Instructions
Step 1: Check Nexus for the Glue Hive Client JAR
Before building, search your Nexus for this critical dependency:
aws-glue-datacatalog-hive3-client
Also search for flink-connector-hive. Note the exact versions available — you may need to update the pom.xml version numbers to match what's in your Nexus.
Step 2: Set up the project
bashcd C:\devhome\projects\flink-access-test

rd /s /q src\main\java\com\example
rd /s /q src\main\java\com\barclays

mkdir src\main\java\com\barclays\poc
Copy the two files:

GlueTableLister.java → src\main\java\com\barclays\poc\GlueTableLister.java
pom.xml → replace the root pom.xml

Step 3: Build
bashmvn clean package -DskipTests
Step 4: Verify
bashjar tf target\glue-table-lister-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar | findstr GlueTableLister
Should show: com/barclays/poc/GlueTableLister.class
Step 5: Upload and run
bashaws s3 cp target\glue-table-lister-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar s3://flink-poc-app-nishikesh/flink-glue-test/glue-table-lister-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
