Important Note
This approach uses HiveCatalog with AWSGlueDataCatalogHiveClientFactory — which is exactly what Anishvaran suggested. But under the hood it still calls the same Glue APIs (GetDatabase, GetTables) on account 767397940910. So it will likely hit the same AccessDenied error unless the target account has added the Glue resource policy.
That said, it's worth trying because the HiveCatalog approach may use a different credential chain or permission path that could work. Share the S3 output with your lead either way — it proves exactly where the blocker is.
